    <string-array name="advices">
        <item>
            GENERAL \n
            Through this application you get to know the Museum of Byzantine Culture of Thessaloniki via a funny treasure hunt. \n
            You should visit every room in the museum, answer the questions and gather all your abilities, in order to solve the riddles you
            come across.\n
            Complete your museum tour with the greatest score.\n\n
            1. Follow the clues on the screen \n
            2. Use the QR code scanner to locate the correct exhibit\n
            3. Fullfill successfully all the questions and the riddles, to increase your score.\n
        </item>
        <item>
            QUIZ GAME\n
            One question, four possible answers. \n
            The only thing you have to do is to find the right one.\n
            How good are you in history?
        </item>
        <item>
            WHERE ARE THE MONUMENTS?\n
            Can you find the location of the monument on the map, knowing the monument and the location name?\n
            Choose the location on the map, as close as possible to the right one, to score more points\n
            The clues you are asking for are hidden on the museum\'s walls
        </item>
        <item>
            CATCH ME IF YOU CAN\n
            The faster your reflexes are the better.\n
            Hit the moving image in order to complete the bigger picture in the end of the game.\n
            The more successful hits you manage, the more points you score and you get a cleaner view at on of the museum\'s masterpieces.
        </item>
        <item>
            SAVE THE ARCHES\n
            In fact it is all about the classic hangman game.\n
            All you have to do is to guess the word before all the arches come down.\n
            What is the words are kind of unusual and Greek, take a good look at your surroundings and the museum will give you the answer
        </item>
        <item>
            ALL COINS HAVE TWO FACES\n
            Can you figure out who they are?\n
            Match them as soon as possible to score points. The more observant you are, the sooner you will finish.\n
            Remember nothing is over until you move on to the next room of the museum.
        </item>
        <item>
            FILL IT UP\n
            Only if you put everything in place you can see what the picture is hidding.\n
            It is a classical puzzle game, also known as "Fast and neatly"
        </item>
        <item>
            FIND THE RIGHT ORDER\n
            Some of the pottery we admire up to this day, took a lot of time in order to look like this and carry all these details.\n
            Put in the rigth order the production stages, their names and form, as fast as you can to increase your score
        </item>
    </string-array>

